# 01_node_tool_toggle — canonical reference test for the substrate.
#
# Two lines. Driven from the Curvz Scripter window. The Node-tool
# ToggleButton on the main toolbar is now addressable as `tb_nod`
# (s188 m1 — funnel migration). It's a normal GTK::ToggleButton
# augmented with the curvz::scripting substrate; clicking it from a
# script goes through the exact same code path as a user click,
# including the radio-invariant logic that sets it as the active tool.
#
# Pre-s188 this script said `tool.node` — the hand-picked name from
# s186 m2 when only the Node button used the wrapper. The migration
# unified GTK widget-names and scriptable names: every tool button is
# addressable by its widget_names.db abbrev (tb_sel, tb_nod, tb_pen, …).
#
# Run this from the Scripter window and check that:
#   1. The Node button visibly turns on in the toolbar.
#   2. The Canvas's active tool becomes Node.
#   3. The assert prints PASS.

tb_nod click
assert tb_nod active == true
